      • drive

        public static void drive(double speed,
                         double rotation)
        Normal method for driving the Go-Kart using WPILib's DifferentialDrive class and arcade style driving.
        Parameters:
        speed - the back and forth output to the drive train [0, 1.0]
        rotation - the rotation output (turning by spinning opposing sides in different directions) [0, 1.0]

      • BAPMdrive

        public static void BAPMdrive(double speed,
                             double rotation)
        BAPM method for driving the Go-Kart normally with the BAPM enabled in certain instances. It only works if the Go-Kart is moving forward and NOT rotating.
        Parameters:
        speed - the back and forth output to the drive train [0, 1.0]
        rotation - the rotation output (turning by spinning opposing sides in different directions) [0, 1.0]
